The paper deals with weighted tree automata, which are commonly studied in formal language theory (cs.FL) and theoretical computer science (cs.THEORY). The paper also discusses the initial algebra semantics and run semantics of these automata, which are related to the study of fixed points and recursion in computer science, respectively. This suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-categories of logic in computer science (cs.LO) and programming languages (cs.PL). Finally, the paper discusses decidability and algorithmic questions related to the properties of these automata, which are often studied in the sub-field of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS).
